As a lead cloud engineer, you will be responsible for architecting and building our backend infrastructure. The Internet-of-Things is a massive challenge, our platform needs to be scalable and able to maintain communication with hundreds of millions of devices simultaneously. You will be working closely with our gateway and mobile engineers to define the necessary backend APIs to support real-time control of thousands of different products.</p>
<p>
<strong>About you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Deep experience building and running fault-tolerant, scalable backend platforms</li>
<li>
Familiar with using and scaling NoSQL databases</li>
<li>
Know how to properly design RESTful and WebSocket based backend interfaces</li>
<li>
Believe in the importance of unit tests and QA</li>
<li>
Expert with JVM based languages (ie Java, Scala, or Groovy)</li>
<li>
Strong understanding of Amazon Web Services (in particular EC2, DynamoDB, S3, and SQS)</li>
<li>
Experience with JVM concurrency</li>
<li>
Strong understanding of security practices to protect user data and prevent unauthorized access</li>
<li>
Passion for working with Big-Data</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Pluses:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with Chef or Puppet</li>
<li>
Familiarity with the design and implementation of frontend web interfaces</li>
<li>
Creativity and passion to do interesting things with internet connected devices</li>
</ul>
