<strong>Who we are:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>
We are a tech start-up company based out of Boulder, CO. Above all else we value playfulness, aspiration, candor, empathy, hard work, transparency and teamwork. We are looking for an individual who embodies all of those characteristics and more.&nbsp; As the office manager, your job is to ensure that the executive team spends zero minutes on anything that isn&rsquo;t related to developing a product, selling, marketing and delivering it. We are looking for an individual who is motivated, self-reliant and will make a positive, energetic addition to our staff.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
5+ years of Quickbooks Premiere or comparable experience is required; experience working with inventory in accounting systems is a plus.</li>
<li>
3+ years of experience with the hiring process, offer letters and HR matters; experience dealing with legal contracts and legal language is a plus</li>
<li>
3+ years experience interacting with banks, bank accounts, etc...</li>
<li>
3+ years experience interacting with PEOs such as Trinet around employee benefits, employee issues and payroll</li>
<li>
3+ years experience procuring IT equipment for employees</li>
<li>
3+ years experience as public interface with great positive and empathetic disposition.</li>
<li>
Ideally has 3+ years experience supervising office administrative workers.</li>
<li>
Ideally has experience facilitating at least one office move</li>
<li>
Passionate about being a team player who establishes trust with respect relationships, meets their commitments and focuses on the company&#39;s outcome</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Execute the financial systems put in place by financial experts (separately employed).</li>
<li>
Execute the hiring processes put in place for EACH new hire.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Interface with landlord and facilities to take care of any facilities problems.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Interface with bank regarding basic transaction logistics and banking needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Search for and procure new office; facilitate move.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Execute processes around NDAs and legal document archival.&nbsp;&nbsp; Interface and execute necessary activities with payroll and health insurers</li>
<li>
Plan for and procure all office needs ranging from furniture, to new employee equipment, to closet supplies.</li>
<li>
Be the point of contact for the non-customer public.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Interface with outsourced IT shop for normal/easy day-to-day IT needs</li>
<li>
Handle non-customer shipping &amp; receiving</li>
<li>
Schedule travel arrangements for employees and help to coordinate shipping of materials, traveling and agenda for trade shows</li>
<li>
Hire and supervise minimum-wage workers who perform menial tasks related to the above responsibilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Handle organization of all our corporate electronic docs, dropbox folder, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Plan for and execute all office-related events such as lunch, happy hours, etc&hellip;</li>
<li>
Maintain general office needs such as ensuring that the fridge stays stocked, handling errand runs, purchases of supplies &amp; food, tidying up the office, cleaning whiteboards, making sure the conference room always looks presentable, and retrieving extra &quot;stuff&quot; to and from off-site storage.</li>
