			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The Role<br />
We are looking for a Operations Analyst to support the head of Manufacturing Operations on day-to-day basis.&nbsp;&nbsp; These tasks may include:</p>
<p>
&bull; Support production engineering for products after transfer from design to high volume production<br />
&bull; Support ongoing execution and development manufacturing test activities<br />
&bull; Interfaces with design, process, test and reliability engineering to solve problems<br />
&bull; Sustains products with cost reduction and yield improvements<br />
&bull; Support component procurement<br />
&bull; Manage inventory flow post production<br />
&bull; Managing suppliers and 3PLs<br />
&bull; Create monthly and ad hoc reports and dashboards for production metrics<br />
&bull; Methodically drive business process improvements to enhance informational speed and accuracy<br />
&bull; Present results of analysis and research on a variety of business operations topics including customer metrics, order management tracking, and capacity utilization trends</p>
<p>
<br />
About You<br />
You are an Excel wiz. &nbsp;In your past work experience, you have worked in a manufacturing facility and are familiar with manufacturing principles in both academic and practice. &nbsp;You have executed and managed manufacturing test processes. &nbsp;Big bonus if you have had Lean Six Sigma training!&nbsp; Given that we are a startup, you must have a strong work ethic and accountability to deadlines; this means no excuses!&nbsp;&nbsp; You must also have strong quantitative, analytical, and organizational skills.&nbsp; Trite but none the less, you must have excellent interpersonal, verbal, and written communications skills.&nbsp; Lastly, you have a profound penchant for problem solving, insatiable desire for learning, and a constant desire to achieve greatness.&nbsp; If this sounds like you, we would love to hear from you.</p>
<p>
Education/Experience<br />
&bull; 4-year degree with a major in engineering, operations management, or related field with exceptional academic achievements<br />
&bull; 4-6 Years of prior relevant work experience</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
